# Image Generation & Asset Pipeline

Generate game assets via Google Gemini API and process them into final sprite files.

## Tool

```bash
GEMINI_API_KEY=$(grep GEMINI_API_KEY .env | cut -d= -f2) \
  node tools/generate-image.mjs "<prompt>" [--out <path>] [--aspect <ratio>] [--model <name>] [--count <n>] [--ref <image>]
```

## Models

| Model | Note |
|-------|------|
| `gemini-3-pro-image-preview` | **Default** — best quality |
| `gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview` | Faster |
| `imagen-4.0-generate-001` | Imagen 4, supports `--negative` |

## Aspect Ratios

`1:1` | `16:9` | `9:16` | `4:3` | `3:4`

## Asset Pipeline (MANDATORY WORKFLOW)

### Step 1: Generate via Gemini

For **sprite sheet** (multiple assets):
```bash
node tools/generate-image.mjs \
  "Pixel art sprite sheet of 8 breakout bricks in horizontal row, evenly spaced on pure black background. Colors: pink, red, orange, gold, green, cyan, blue, purple. Each brick ~2.5:1 aspect ratio, neon style, dark outline. No text." \
  --out public/assets/games/breakout/bricks-sheet.png \
  --aspect 4:3
```

For **single asset**:
```bash
node tools/generate-image.mjs \
  "Pixel art paddle bar for breakout game. Neon cyan, wide flat rectangle, white highlight, dark outline, glow. Pure black background. No text." \
  --out public/assets/games/breakout/paddle-raw.png \
  --aspect 16:9
```

#### Prompting Rules
- **Always specify background**: `pure black background` or `pure white background`
- **Always add** `No text, no other elements`
- **Specify proportions**: `~2.5:1 aspect ratio`, `7 times wider than tall`
- **Style**: `pixel art`, `8-bit`, `retro arcade`, `neon glowing`
- **PixelDen colors**: cyan `#00FFF2`, magenta `#FF00E4`, dark bg `#0A0E17`
- **Aspect ratio**: `4:3` for sprite sheets, `16:9` for wide assets, `1:1` for square

### Step 2: Process via `process-sprites.mjs`

**ALWAYS** process after generating. Gemini generates large images (~1408x768) with lots of empty space.

```bash
node tools/process-sprites.mjs <input> [options]
```

**Options:**
| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--out <path>` | Output path (default: overwrite input; with `--split`: prefix) |
| `--bg <black\|white>` | Background color to remove (default: auto-detect) |
| `--threshold <n>` | Detection threshold (default: 20) |
| `--split` | Split sheet into individual sprites |
| `--names <a,b,c>` | Names for split sprites (default: 0,1,2...) |
| `--square` | Pad to square |
| `--pad <n>` | Padding around content (default: 2) |

### Step 3: Cleanup

```bash
rm -f *-raw.png *-sheet.png *-gen.png *-new.png
```

## Asset Storage

| Type | Path |
|------|------|
| Game sprites | `public/assets/games/{slug}/{asset}.png` |
| Game thumbnail | `public/assets/games/{slug}/thumbnail.png` |
| Hero banner | `public/assets/placeholders/hero-banner.png` |

## Phaser Sprite Sizing

Gemini generates large images (800-1400px). In Phaser they display small (40x16, 80x12, etc).

**ALWAYS in code:**
```typescript
sprite.setDisplaySize(TARGET_W, TARGET_H);
// For dynamic body:
sprite.body!.setSize(TARGET_W, TARGET_H);
// For STATIC body (bricks) -- MANDATORY:
(sprite.body as Phaser.Physics.Arcade.StaticBody).setSize(W, H);
(sprite.body as Phaser.Physics.Arcade.StaticBody).updateFromGameObject();
```

Without `updateFromGameObject()` on static bodies, physics hitbox will be at wrong position!
